summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 2372, entitled "An Ordinance to regulate and restrain the selling of fruits, sweet meats, beverages and other commodities and maintaining of stands and other objects for the sale thereof on certain streets, and public grounds of the City of Seattle, declaring a nuisance and punishing violations thereof", approved September 27, 1892 and Ordinance No. 4954, approved June 20, 1898, amendatory thereof.
